#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
foctl — Citadel unified deployment tool.

FOUR DEPLOYMENT MODES:

  docker      Docker Compose on this machine — no Kubernetes needed.
              Single port (80) via nginx reverse proxy.
              Best for: laptop, single-server, quick evaluation, air-gapped.

  helm        Deploy the app (api/processor/frontend) via the Helm umbrella
              chart (charts/citadel). App-only — bring your own substrate
              (ES/Redis/MinIO) via config.json's `substrate` block. Reuses your
              existing ingress (traefik/tailscale/nginx) via access.ingress_class.
              Best for: clusters that already run substrate + an ingress.

  k8s         Deploy to a Kubernetes cluster reachable via kubectl (raw
              manifests — also provisions ES/Redis/MinIO in-namespace).
              Best for: staging / production clusters (GKE, EKS, AKS,
              k3s bare-metal, Rancher, OpenShift ...).

  k8s-new     Create a local k3d cluster (runs inside Docker), then deploy.
              Best for: development machines, CI pipelines, offline labs.
              Requires Docker.

USAGE:
  ./foctl                          Interactive menu
  ./foctl deploy docker            Docker Compose deployment
  ./foctl deploy helm              Helm chart (app-only; bring-your-own substrate)
  ./foctl deploy k8s               Deploy to the current kubectl context
  ./foctl deploy k8s-new           Create k3d cluster then deploy

  ./foctl deploy k8s --no-build    Skip Docker image build
  ./foctl deploy k8s --no-cache    Force full Docker rebuild (ignore cache)
  ./foctl deploy k8s --restart     Re-apply manifests + restart pods only
  ./foctl deploy k8s --setup-traefik  Also apply kube-system Traefik config

  ./foctl status  [docker|k8s]     Health check
  ./foctl logs    <svc> [mode]     Stream logs: api | processor | frontend | all
  ./foctl update  [docker|k8s]     Rebuild images + redeploy
  ./foctl destroy [docker|k8s]     Tear everything down (confirms first)
  ./foctl config                   Show parsed configuration

All Kubernetes settings are in config.json.
Docker settings are in .env (created from .env.example on first run).
"""

